Typedef Documentation

typedef TUint32 TLbsConversionPluginCapabilityMask

Conversion plugin's capabilities

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum _TLbsConversionPluginCapabilityMask

Enums that are used as bitmasks to define the capabilities of the conversion plugin.

Enumerator:
ELbsPluginCapabilityNotDefined 

Bitmask indicating the conversion plugin's capability has not been defined.

ELbsPluginCapabilityPosInfo 

Bitmask indicating the conversion plugin's capability to use position information for the conversion.

ELbsPluginCapabilityGsmInfo 

Bitmask indicating the conversion plugin's capability to use GSM cell information for the conversion.

ELbsPluginCapabilityWcdmaInfo 

Bitmask indicating the conversion plugin's capability to use WCDMA cell information for the conversion.

ELbsPluginCapabilityWlanInfo 

Bitmask indicating the conversion plugin's capability to use WLAN AP information for the conversion.

ELbsPluginCapabilityAreaInfoAll 

Bitmask indicating the conversion plugin's capability to use all area information for the conversion.
